data.body: There should be a yes/no confirmation when deleting a component, as well as a "don't show me this again" checkbox.

data.body:
If the text is too long it gets cut off. This prevents users from seeing the whole name/description of a setting.

data.title: Check for unsaved changes before closing a project
data.body:
If a project gets closed with unsaved changes to a scene or script file, all changes made to that file are gone.

Add a confirmation dialog to allow the user to save changes before closing, or close without saving.

We could also add an auto-save to scene files when the player is launched, the same way the script files behave.

data.title: Windows editor crashes on nonexistent Android API refresh
data.body:
Runtime context: Windows 10, community editor activated with free product key, Android Studio is not installed

Steps to reproduce: Create new 3D project (may work with any template or openable project), go to Build -> Build Settings -> Android -> (Android API) Refresh button

Result: editor crashes with WIndows dialog popup (program *.exe has stopped working - clicking Cancel exits)

Expected behavior: popup dialog/console message "I can't find any Android development tools with your setup, please accept my condolences.", or nothing
